# Performer's working config -- untracked so they can edit it (MIDI bindings,
# tempo tweaks) without git-pull conflicts. lib/setup.scd seeds it from the
# tracked data_original/ on a fresh clone. Edit data_original/ to ship updates.
# No trailing slash: on the composer's machine data is a SYMLINK to data_original
# (so live SC saves flow straight into the tracked seed), and a bare `data/` rule
# would only match a real directory, not the symlink. `/data` ignores either.
/data

# MIDI cue source files (binary, managed outside git) -- but the runtime cue
# source MUST ship so the cellist's git pull can actually play (else the cue
# sheet points at a missing file and SimpleMIDIFile throws "_FilePos failed").
*.mid
*.midi
!midi/MIDICues.mid

# Audio media (sound files used while experimenting -- large binaries, not
# part of the runtime; kept locally only). lib/sounds/ is the experimentation
# scratch dir -- ignored wholesale -- but metroblock.wav is a RUNTIME dependency
# (the \metroCue voice loads it at engine boot) so it must ship.
lib/sounds/
!lib/sounds/metroblock.wav
*.wav
*.flac
*.aif
*.aiff
*.mp3
*.ogg

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Reaper project backups / autosaves and rendered media
reaper/AutoSaves/
reaper/Backups/
reaper/Media/
reaper/old/
*.rpp-bak

# Generated extraction output (review, then copy into data/)
reaper/extracted/
